The paper deals with algorithmic approaches to binary linear classification and feature selection, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning and data mining communities. The use of the generalized approximate message passing (GAMP) algorithm, which is a recent development in the field of compressive sensing, is a key aspect of the paper. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses applications of the proposed approaches to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI), which are additional possible sub-categories.
